# Trivy IaC misconfig suppressions — each entry is a documented, deliberate exception.
#
# AZU-0012 — "No network rules defined and default action allows access."
# Only fires on the Terraform state backend account (bootstrap/main.tf), which
# must stay reachable from CI/local for the azurerm backend. A default-Deny ACL
# without the runner's egress IPs would lock out state operations. The application
# storage module (modules/storage) DOES define network_rules with default_action
# = "Deny", so this suppression is scoped in practice to the bootstrap account.
AZU-0012
